Usage: monitor_hosts [-help] [-gstack_duration <integer>]
                     [-gstack_interval <integer>] [-gstack_start <integer>]
                     [-log <string>] [-overwrite] [-period <integer>]

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-gstack_duration <integer>         # -gstack_duration <seconds>, Time duration
                                   # in seconds for which we want gstack to be
                                   # logged. (Default: End of the Program !)
                                   # (int, optional)
-gstack_interval <integer>         # -gstack_interval <seconds>, Time interval
                                   # in seconds between repeated gstack logs
                                   # during the gstack duration. (Default: 60)
                                   # (int, optional)
-gstack_start <integer>            # -gstack_start <seconds>, Time in seconds
                                   # after which the gstack is started to be
                                   # logged. (Default: 60) (int, optional)
-log <string>                      # Log file name. Default: host-monitor.log
                                   # (string, optional)
-overwrite                         # Overwrite the log file if it already
                                   # exists (bool, optional)
-period <integer>                  # Sampling period in seconds. Default: 60.
                                   # (int, optional)